==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piecemeal
<hw>Piece"meal`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>pecemele</ets>; <ets>pece</ets> a piece + AS. <ets>m<?/lum</ets>,
dat. pl. of <ets>m<?/l</ets> part. See <er>Meal</er> a portion.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>In pieces; in parts or fragments.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧On which
it <xex>piecemeal</xex> brake.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The beasts will tear thee <qex>piecemeal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Piece by piece; by little and little in
succession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Piecemeal</qex> they win, this acre first, than that.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piecemeal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Piecemeal
<hw>Piece"meal`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made up of parts or pieces;
single; separate.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧These <xex>piecemeal</xex> guilts.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Gov. of Tongue.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piecemeal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Piecemeal
<hw>Piece"meal`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A fragment; a scrap.</def>
<rj><au>R. Vaughan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piecemealed</ent>⟦br⟧
